** About Us **

Teys Australia is an innovative Australian food business with home grown pride
and global reach. Drawing on more than 70 years’ experience in the beef
industry, our team of over 4,500 focus their energy and expertise on
delivering value to our communities, customers, and consumers.

As one the leading beef processors and exporters in Australia, we are a proud
partner to over 7,000 Aussie beef producers and some of the largest names in
fresh food retailing in the country. In a joint venture with Cargill, Teys
Australia has retained its strong founding family connections and it is this
rich heritage that drives our future.

** About the Role **

Teys Australia Food Solutions (TAFS) are seeking a qualified ** Quality
Assurance Coordinator ** to join the Quality team based at our
Morningside/Hemmant processing sites in QLD. The main focus of this role is to
maintain the integrity of the food safety, compliance and quality requirements
to ensure our customers’ expectations are met. The role will also perform as
the second in charge to the Quality Assurance (QA) Manager.

Additional role requirements include:

  * Review results of third-party lab for samples/swabs and verification. 
  * Daily review and completion of pre-shipment paperwork prior to release for dispatch. 
  * Assist HACCP team to maintain quality control standards in line with the operational requirements. 
  * Manage and ensure calibration schedule for all testing equipment is completed by staff responsible. 
  * Assist QA Manager in the completion of internal audits (Systems/CCP’s/GMP) and external audits (announced/unannounced). 
  * Provide input and support in relation to Work Instructions and training operators. 
  * Ensure work procedures and all other form changes are documented and communicated to key staff. 

** About You ** _ ** ** _   
It is _ ** essential ** _ that you have the following experience/skills:

  * Qualifications and experience in HACCP Principles & Practices. 
  * Previous experience to BRC, SFP Qld, DAWE, WSEP and CFMSR standards. 
  * A “can do” attitude and willingness to learn. 
  * Demonstrated ability to write work instructions. 
  * Strong interpersonal skills and the ability to pro-actively seek out opportunities for improvement. 
  * Demonstrated ability to communicate with all levels of staff, both technical and non-technical personnel with regards to food safety and quality matters. 
  * Own transport to be able to support two sites, as required. 

_ Desirable: _

  * Tertiary qualification in Food Science/Food Technology (or similar discipline) 
  * Intermediate level computer literacy - Microsoft Office suite 
  * Sound navigation knowledge of Uni-Works, Information Leader (iLeader) 
  * Internal and/or external auditing experience. 
  * Experience in the Ready to Eat Small-goods and Meat Processing industries. 
  * Experience in a High-Risk production environment 
  * Knowledge of the relevant Australian Standards, FSANZ Food Standards Code and various State regulations 

** What’s in it for you? **

  * Competitive salary 
  * Annual bonus opportunity 
  * Access to meat purchasing credit program 
  * Free parking 
  * Salary packaging - electronic devices, novated car leasing, superannuation 
  * Injury/Illness salary continuance scheme 
  * Access to a range of corporate discounts 

